The paper deals with the construction and properties of cyclic codes over a specific ring, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of DNA codes also has applications in cryptography (cs.CR) and data storage (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the $GC$-content of the codes, which is a topic in computational biology (cs.SI).
